{
  "texts": [
    "The following assumptions on the elastic collision kernels (B ij) 1≤i,j≤4 are the same considered in [21].",
    "(EL1) They satisfy a symmetry property when interchanging the species indices i and jB ij (|v -v * |, cos θ) = B ji (|v -v * |, cos θ), ∀v, v * ∈ R 3, ∀θ ∈ [0, π].",
    "(EL2) They write as the product of a kinetic part Φ ij ≥ 0 and an angular part b ij > 0, namelyB ij (|v -v * |, cos θ) = Φ ij (|v -v * |)b ij (cos θ), ∀v, v * ∈ R 3, ∀θ ∈ [0, π].",
    "(EL3) For the kinetic part, we assume that there exists a constant γ ∈ [0, 1] such thatΦ ij (|v -v * |) = C ij |v -v * | γ, C ij > 0, ∀v, v * ∈ R 3.",
    "(EL4) We suppose that the angular part is positive for a.e."
  ]
}